## ‚ö†Ô∏è CRITICAL RULE: Verified Information Only

**NEVER UNDER ANY CIRCUMSTANCE INCLUDE INFORMATION THAT IS NOT VERIFIED. NEVER SAY STUFF THAT WE DIDN'T DO.**

### Mandatory Guidelines:
- ‚ùå **NEVER** claim to have tested products unless you actually did
- ‚ùå **NEVER** claim to have conducted research, studies, or trials that weren't performed
- ‚ùå **NEVER** use first-person language for actions not taken ("we tested", "our testing", "we found")
- ‚úÖ **ALWAYS** attribute findings to credible external sources
- ‚úÖ **ALWAYS** use phrases like: "Based on research done by X...", "According to dermatologist reviews...", "Expert analysis shows...", "Published studies indicate..."
- ‚úÖ **ALWAYS** cite real sources when referencing studies, tests, or expert opinions

**Examples:**
- ‚ùå BAD: "We tested 12 products during 4 weeks and measured hydration levels"
- ‚úÖ GOOD: "Based on dermatologist reviews and clinical studies published in the Journal of Cosmetic Dermatology, these 12 products show measurable hydration improvements"
- ‚ùå BAD: "Our testing methodology involved corneometer measurements"
- ‚úÖ GOOD: "According to independent lab testing and consumer feedback analysis..."

---

## Overview & Philosophy

### What is a Deep Dive Post?

Deep dive posts are **comprehensive, research-backed articles** that:
- Provide **extensive analysis** and detailed explanations
- Include **multiple images** (8-15+) throughout the content
- Feature **longer paragraphs** with rich, flowing prose
- Offer **in-depth insights** backed by research and expert opinions
- Use **visual storytelling** to enhance understanding
- Maintain **reader engagement** through varied content formats

### Ideal Length
- **3,000 - 8,000+ words**
- **10-20 sections** with subsections
- **8-15+ images** strategically placed

---

## Base Structure

### Complete Wrapper
```html
<div class="prose prose-lg lg:prose-xl max-w-none">
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <!-- Table of Contents -->
  <!-- Introduction -->
  <!-- Main Content Sections -->
  <!-- Conclusion -->
  <!-- Related Resources -->
</div>
```

### Hero Section with Featured Image
```html
<div class="not-prose mb-12">
  <!-- Featured Image -->
  <div class="relative w-full h-[500px] rounded-2xl overflow-hidden shadow-2xl mb-8">
    <img
      src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-example?w=1200&h=500&fit=crop"
      alt="Descriptive alt text for accessibility"
      class="w-full h-full object-cover"
    />
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-t from-black/60 to-transparent flex items-end">
      <div class="p-8">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Complete Guide Title</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-white/90">Compelling subtitle that hooks the reader</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Article Metadata -->
  <div class="flex items-center justify-between text-sm text-gray-600 mb-8">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
      <span>By <strong class="text-gray-900">Author Name</strong></span>
      <span>‚Ä¢</span>
      <span>January 15, 2025</span>
      <span>‚Ä¢</span>
      <span>15 min read</span>
    </div>
    <div class="flex gap-2">
      <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-blue-100 text-blue-800 rounded-full text-xs font-medium">Category</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
```

