## Typography & Paragraphs

### Opening Paragraph (Hook)
```html
<p class="text-xl leading-relaxed text-gray-800 mb-8 font-medium">
  <strong>Start with a compelling hook</strong> that draws readers into the topic. This opening paragraph should be larger, bolder, and immediately capture attention while setting the stage for the deep dive ahead.
</p>
```

### Standard Body Paragraphs
```html
<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-700 mb-6">
  Regular body paragraphs should flow naturally with a conversational yet authoritative tone. Each paragraph should explore a single idea thoroughly, typically containing 3-5 sentences. Use transitional phrases to connect ideas smoothly and maintain narrative flow throughout the article.
</p>

<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-700 mb-6">
  Continue with related thoughts in subsequent paragraphs. Deep dive posts benefit from well-developed ideas that give readers time to absorb complex concepts. Don't rush through topics‚Äîallow the narrative to breathe and develop naturally.
</p>
```

### Emphasis Within Paragraphs
```html
<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-700 mb-6">
  Use <strong class="font-semibold text-gray-900">bold text</strong> for key terms and important concepts. Use <em class="italic">italics</em> for subtle emphasis or foreign terms. For critical information that must stand out, use <span class="bg-yellow-100 px-1 py-0.5 rounded">highlighted text</span> sparingly.
</p>
```

### Section Introduction Paragraphs
```html
<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-800 mb-8 bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-400 p-6 rounded-r-lg">
  <strong>Section Overview:</strong> Each major section can begin with a highlighted introductory paragraph that previews what readers will learn. This helps with scanability and sets clear expectations for the content ahead.
</p>
```

